post_text:
As you may have heard, Governor Roy Cooper has ordered all k-12 schools in North Carolina to close for at least two weeks.

Therefore, Francine Delany New School for Children will be closed March 16- March 30, 2020.

Monday and Tuesday will be used as teacher workdays. All families should receive an email from your child‚Äôs teacher by Wednesday morning at 9:00am with directions for how distant learning will look for your child. Our hope is that students continue with learning during this interruption in face to face learning.

If you do not receive information from your child‚Äôs teacher by Wednesday morning at 9:00, please email your child‚Äôs teacher.

Francine Delany New School for Children's after school program will be closed March 16-March 30 as well.

All staff, please be on the lookout for an email to be sent by 9:00 tonight with more details about what the next two weeks will look like for you.

What happens when the school bus arrives to an on-the-ground school without desks? Our friends at Francine Delany New School For Children came to the BeLoved Village where we talked about the history of housing, the housing crisis in Asheville, racial and economic justice, and how youth are being the change! They got lots of awesome work done at the Village! We learned, had fun, and worked to bring our neighbors in need HOME! Now that's a good day!

BeLoved Asheville
December 2, 2019 at 9:36 AM ¬∑

Did you know this year BeLoved provided educational and enrichment programs for nearly 2,000 area youth? Whether it is youth leadership development, civic engagement including speaking at City Council and County Commission, teaching about the housing crisis in Asheville and how youth can be the change, sharing history and cultural programs, activities and workshops in music and the arts, and hands-on service projects that make a difference in the community. When you give to BeLoved you support these kind of positive programs to stir young minds and hearts! Join in giving to BeLoved today to support our youth at www.belovedasheville.com

shared_text:
BeLoved Asheville
September 28, 2019 at 8:44 AM ¬∑

What an amazing time we had at Francine Delany New School For Children on Friday! We met with the upper grades to share more about our BeLoved Village and tell the stories of people we know and love who are living through the housing crisis! We believe that youth are not just the future but the NOW in making changes to help solve tough community problems.

We love sharing this program with schools and youth groups about what home means using art. And we have the youth brainstorm about how to use their super powers to help us build a home in the Beloved Village! These students were super engaged and are ready to be the change to create deeply affordable homes that are community-oriented, sustainable, and produce equity! Will you join them?

#avl #828isgreat #belovedvillage #kidsbuild #kidpower #avlart #love828

post_text:
Today school was not in session but we still had over 20 percent of our students show up for the First Annual MLK Jr day of service!! Fifteen Project Power Americorps members, lots of parents and teachers showed up and helped make posters to prep for the MLK Jr Peace March. Students attended the service before the march, marched and then the middle school students went to Asheville Nursing & Rehabilitation Center and spent time with the residents talking about the march and why it was important for them to participate. Some of the residents shared their life experiences. The residents wanted the kids to sing so Ms. Melissa led the group in singing Love Can Build a Bridge, our school song!!
We are so proud of how the students jumped in and got involved. Our future looks bright folks!
text:

Some of the residents shared their life experiences. The residents wanted the kids to sing so Ms. Melissa led the group in singing Love Can Build a Bridge, our school song!!
We are so proud of how the students jumped in and got involved. Our future looks bright folks!
